board-init.propertiesInfo:
A sprite property is a characteristic of a sprite such as its speed, its width,...
It has a type: number, string (text) or boolean (true or false).
Its value can be accessed as follow: mySpriteName.propertyName;
Its value can be modified by assigning a new one.
Example: myHero.speed = 500;
It has a default value, so it is not mandatory to set it.
